I am building cefpython on Mac using various Python versions (2.7, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6) and only on Python 3.6 I get lots of warnings (about 300) like this:

```
cefpython.cpp:114014:20: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        } else if (sizeof(cef_errorcode_t) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114011:20: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        } else if (sizeof(cef_errorcode_t) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114009:13: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        if (sizeof(cef_errorcode_t) < sizeof(long)) {
            ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114059:19: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
                  ^
cefpython.cpp:114053:20: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        } else if (sizeof(cef_urlrequest_status_t) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114045:20: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        } else if (sizeof(cef_urlrequest_status_t) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114042:20: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        } else if (sizeof(cef_urlrequest_status_t) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
cefpython.cpp:114040:13: warning: will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        if (sizeof(cef_urlrequest_status_t) < sizeof(long)) {
```

This happens only on Mac and with Python 3.6.0. I build on Linux with 3.6.0 and I don't see these.

Cython: 0.25.2
OS: MacOS 10.9 Mavericks
XCode: 5.1
